<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>16198</anchor> <rss>jms-009U.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-009U</addr>  <route>jms-009U.xml</route>   <title>SANDWICH Seminar</title> <meta name="venue">Computer Laboratory, <link href="ucam.xml" type="local" title="University of Cambridge">University of Cambridge</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p><em>Scientists Are Now Discussing Wildly Interesting Conjectures and Hypotheses</em></p><p>The SANDWICH seminar runs on Mondays at 1pm in the Computer Science department, in room FS07 . This is an internal seminar series of the Cambridge Logical Structures Hub.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>16199</anchor> <rss>ucam.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Institution</taxon> <addr>ucam</addr>  <route>ucam.xml</route>   <title>University of Cambridge</title> <meta name="external">https://www.cam.ac.uk/</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>16200</anchor> <rss>2023-10-02.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-10-02</addr>  <route>2023-10-02.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-10-02</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Today I have <link href="sanjivranchod.xml" type="local" title="Sanjiv Ranchod">Sanjiv Ranchod</link>’s first year viva as well as the <link href="jms-009U.xml" type="local" title="SANDWICH Seminar">SANDWICH Seminar</link>.</p><p>I am thinking that it would be good to write a blog post about how daily journaling can fit into a successful scientific workflow; it would be good to think a bit more about whether <link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" title="Forester">Forester</link> can be adapted to more directly serve this use-case.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>